9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 238, L.D. 338, “An Act to Increase the
10 Size and Balance of Jury Pools”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 1 in the 2nd and 3rd lines (page 1, lines 5 and
12 6 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "persons to whom state income tax forms have
13 been mailed,"
14 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 1 in the last line (page 1, line 11 in L.D.) by
15 inserting after the following: "Court." the following: 'For purposes of this subsection,
16 "public assistance" has the same meaning as in Title 19-A, section 2605, subsection 1,
17 paragraph A.'
18 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
19 'Sec. 2. Effective date. This Act takes effect January 1, 2028.'
20 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
21 number to read consecutively.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment removes the bill's requirement that the list of persons to whom state
2244 income tax forms have been mailed be added to the source list of prospective jurors in each
2255 county. It also clarifies that the recipients of public assistance benefits who must be added
2266 to the source list of prospective jurors in each county include recipients of medical
2277 assistance, recipients of state supplemental income for blind, disabled or elderly persons,
2288 recipients of temporary assistance for needy families and participants in the Parents as
2299 Scholars Program. The amendment delays until January 1, 2028 the changes made in the
3300 Legislation.
